Package com.project.bean

Class DietPlan

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.project.bean.DietPlan
  • public class DietPlan
extends java.lang.Object
    DietPlan represents a diet plan for a user and contains the various food items he needs to consume in the time span of the diet. Each DietPlan contains vegetarian, non-Vegetarian and fruit items with whom this class has a one-to-many association. Each of the vegetarian, non-vegetarian and fruit items will exist if the DietPlan for them exists.
    Author:
    Harsh Sharma

      • getTotalCaloriesOfDiet

        public double getTotalCaloriesOfDiet​(java.util.ArrayList<VegItems> veg,
                                     java.util.ArrayList<NonVegItems> nonVeg,
                                     java.util.ArrayList<FruitItems> fruit)
        Returns the total calories of the diet that is calculated by adding the total calories of individual vegetarian, non-vegetarian and fruit items in the diet plan. The method loops through the list of the types of food items and adds there total calories to get the final total calories of the diet plan.
        Parameters:
        veg - An ArrayList of VegItems objects.
        nonVeg - An ArrayList of NonVegItems objects.
        fruit - An ArrayList of FruitItems objects.
        Returns:
        double The total calculated calories of the diet plan.
